16 (Ireland)]]\n* [[List of number-one albums of 2016 (Australia)]]\n* [[List of UK Albums Chart number ones of the 2010s]]\n* [[List of UK R&B Albums Chart number ones of 2016]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Discogs master|992029|Lemonade}}\n* [http://libguides.mica.edu/lemonade Beyonc\u00e9's 'Lemonade' and Information Resources], a Resource Guide from the [[Maryland Institute College of Art]]\n* {{IMDB_title|5662106|Beyonc\u00e9: Lemonade}}\n\n{{Beyonc\u00e9|state=collapsed}}\n{{IFPI Global Year-End}}\n{{Grammy Award for Best Urban Contemporany Album}}\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lemonade (Beyonce album)}}\n[[Category:2010s musical films]]\n[[Category:2016 albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Diplo]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Jack White]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Just Blaze]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Mike Will Made It]]\n[[Category:Albums recorded at Record Plant (Los Angeles)]]\n[[Category:Beyonc\u00e9 albums]]\n[[Category:Beyonc\u00e9 video albums]]\n[[Category:Columbia Records albums]]\n[[Category:Concept albums]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Beyonc\u00e9]]\n[[Category:Peabody Award-winning broadcasts]]\n[[Category:Grammy Award for Best Urban Contemporary Album]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Beyonc\u00e9]]\n", "name_user": "Bgkc4444", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fixed typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lemonade_(Beyonc%C3%A9_album)"}
{"title_page": "Ghosal hematodiaphyseal dysplasia", "text_new": "{{Infobox medical condition (new)\n| name            = Ghosal hematodiaphyseal dysplasia\n| synonyms        = GHDD<ref>{{cite web |title=OMIM Entry - # 231095 - GHOSAL HEMATODIAPHYSEAL DYSPLASIA; GHDD |url=https://omim.org/entry/231095 |website=omim.org |accessdate=14 April 2019}}</ref>\n| image           = Thromboxane A2 acsv.svg\n| alt             = \n| caption         = [[Thromboxane A2]]\n| pronounce       = \n| field           = \n| symptoms        = \n| complications   = \n| onset           = \n| duration        = \n| types           = \n| causes          = \n| risks           = \n| diagnosis       = \n| differential    = \n| prevention      = \n| treatment       = \n| medication      = \n| prognosis       = \n| frequency       = \n| deaths          = \n}}\n'''Ghosal hematodiaphyseal dysplasia,''' is a rare, [[Autosome|autosomal]] recessive disease, characterized by diaphyseal dysplasia and metaphyseal dysplasia of the long bones and refractory [[anemia]].<ref name=\"pmid17203301\">{{cite journal |last1=Isidor |first1=B. |last2=Dagoneau |first2=N. |last3=Huber |first3=C. |last4=Genevieve |first4=D. |last5=Bader-Meunier |first5=B. |last6=Blanche |first6=S. |last7=Picard |first7=C. |last8=De Vernejoul |first8=M. C. |last9=Munnich |first9=A. |last10=Le Merrer |first10=M. |last11=Cormier-Daire |first11=V. |title=A gene responsible for Ghosal hemato-diaphyseal dysplasia maps to chromosome 7q33\u201334 |journal=Human Genetics |date=3 January 2007 |volume=121 |issue=2 |pages=269\u2013273 |doi=10.1007/s00439-006-0311-1 |pmid=17203301 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Alebouyeh |first1=Mardawig |last2=Vossough |first2=Parvanch |last3=Tabarrok |first3=Firouz |title=Early Manifestation of Ghosal-Type Hemato-Diaphyseal Dysplasia |journal=Pediatric Hematology and Oncology |date=9 July 2009 |volume=20 |issue=5 |pages=409\u2013415 |doi=10.1080/08880010390203945 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://omim.org/clinicalSynopsis/231095|title=OMIM Clinical Synopsis - #231095 - GHOSAL HEMATODIAPHYSEAL DYSPLASIA; GHDD|website=omim.org|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\nIt is associated with a deficiency of [[Thromboxane-A synthase]],<ref name=\"pmid18264100\">{{cite journal |last1=Genevi\u00e8ve |first1=David |last2=Proulle |first2=Val\u00e9rie |last3=Isidor |first3=Bertrand |last4=Bellais |first4=Samuel |last5=Serre |first5=Val\u00e9rie |last6=Djouadi |first6=Fatima |last7=Picard |first7=Capucine |last8=Vignon-Savoye |first8=Capucine |last9=Bader-Meunier |first9=Brigitte |last10=Blanche |first10=St\u00e9phane |last11=de Vernejoul |first11=Marie-Christine |last12=Legeai-Mallet |first12=Laurence |last13=Fischer |first13=Anne-Marie |last14=Le Merrer |first14=Martine |last15=Dreyfus |first15=Marie |last16=Gaussem |first16=Pascale |last17=Munnich |first17=Arnold |last18=Cormier-Daire |first18=Val\u00e9rie |title=Thromboxane synthase mutations in an increased bone density disorder (Ghosal syndrome) |journal=Nature Genetics |date=10 February 2008 |volume=40 |issue=3 |pages=284\u2013286 |doi=10.1038/ng.2007.66 |pmid=18264100 }}</ref> which produces [[Thromboxane A2]].\n\nAlthough this disease is like [[Camurati\u2013Engelmann disease|Camurati-Engelman disease]] where there is also diaphyseal dysplasia, there are, however, reasons to differentiate between the two diseases. As mentioned earlier, both diseases affect diaphysis, but Ghosal hematodiaphyseal dysplasia, affects both the diaphysis, and metaphyses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://omim.org/entry/231095|title=OMIM Entry - # 231095 - GHOSAL HEMATODIAPHYSEAL DYSPLASIA; GHDD|website=omim.org|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> Also, [[Camurati\u2013Engelmann disease|Camurati-Engelman disease]] has no sign of defective [[Haematopoiesis|hematopoiesis]], but Ghosal hematodiaphyseal dysplasia is associated with a [[Hematologic disease|hematological abnormality]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Datta |first1=Kalpana |last2=Karmakar |first2=Madan |last3=Hira |first3=Michael |last4=Halder |first4=Sanjay |last5=Pramanik |first5=Koushik |last6=Banerjee |first6=Goutam |title=Ghosal Hematodiaphyseal Dysplasia with Myelofibrosis |journal=The Indian Journal of Pediatrics |date=15 September 2012 |volume=80 |issue=12 |pages=1050\u20131052 |doi=10.1007/s12098-012-0872-z |pmid=22983925 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Arora |first1=Richa |last2=Aggarwal |first2=Shagun |last3=Deme |first3=Swaroopa |title=Ghosal hematodiaphyseal dysplasia\u2014a concise review including an illustrative patient |journal=Skeletal Radiology |date=30 August 2014 |volume=44 |issue=3 |pages=447\u2013450 |doi=10.1007/s00256-014-1989-0 |pmid=25172219 }}</ref>\n\nThis is a rare disease and was characterized in 1988, with not many cases reported.<ref name=\"pmid3385529\">{{cite journal |last1=Ghosal |first1=S.P. |last2=Mukherjee |first2=A.K. |last3=Mukherjee |first3=D. |last4=Ghosh |first4=A.K. |title=Diaphyseal dysplasia associated with anemia |journal=The Journal of Pediatrics |date=July 1988 |volume=113 |issue=1 |pages=49\u201357 |doi=10.1016/s0022-3476(88)80527-4 |pmid=3385529 }}</ref> Most cases are found in India and the Middle East area, likely meaning a shared gene pool.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Jeevan |first1=Amrit |last2=Doyard |first2=Mathilde |last3=Kabra |first3=Madhulika |last4=Daire |first4=Valerie Cormier |last5=Gupta |first5=Neerja |title=Ghosal type hematodiaphyseal dysplasia |journal=Indian Pediatrics |date=16 April 2016 |volume=53 |issue=4 |pages=347\u2013348 |doi=10.1007/s13312-016-0851-y |pmid=27156553 }}</ref>\n\n== Symptoms ==\n\n== Causes ==\nGhosal hematodiaphyseal dysplasia is an inherited [[Autosome|autosomal]] recessive disorder due to a [[mutation]] in both copies of the TBXAS1 gene on [[chromosome]] 7q34. The TBXAS1 gene codes for the enzyme [[Thromboxane-A synthase]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://omim.org/entry/274180|title=OMIM Entry - * 274180 - THROMBOXANE A SYNTHASE 1; TBXAS1|website=omim.org|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\nThis enzyme has a couple of essential functions in the body that, if removed, could lead to the symptoms observed with the disease. [[Thromboxane-A synthase]] is responsible for platelet aggregation and the regulation of bone mineral density. [[Thromboxane-A synthase]] regulates bone mineral density by influencing the two [[Gene|genes]] TNFSF\u2081\u2081 and TNFSF\u2081\u2081B, which encode for RANKL and osteoclastogenesis inhibitory factor in [[Osteoblast|osteoblasts]], so if the regulation did not occur it consequently leads to [[Sclerosis (medicine)|sclerosis]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Ciftciler |first1=Rafiye |last2=Buyukas\u0131k |first2=Yahya |last3=Saglam |first3=Emine Arzu |last4=Haznedaroglu |first4=Ibrahim Celalettin |title=Ghosal hematodiaphyseal dysplasia with autoimmune anemia in two adult siblings |journal=Transfusion and Apheresis Science |date=1 August 2019 |volume=58 |issue=4 |pages=449\u2013452 |doi=10.1016/j.transci.2019.04.027 |pmid=31395426 }}</ref>\n\nThe refractory [[anemia]] also called [[corticosteroid]] sensitive [[anemia]], is likely due to fibrotic scarring or [[Sclerosis (medicine)|sclerosis]], which is the stiffening of the [[Tissue (biology)|tissue]] when organ-specific [[Tissue (biology)|tissue]] is replaced with [[connective tissue]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Arora |first1=Richa |last2=Aggarwal |first2=Shagun |last3=Deme |first3=Swaroopa |title=Ghosal hematodiaphyseal dysplasia\u2014a concise review including an illustrative patient |journal=Skeletal Radiology |date=30 August 2014 |volume=44 |issue=3 |pages=447\u2013450 |doi=10.1007/s00256-014-1989-0 |pmid=25172219 }}</ref>\n\n== Treatment ==\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n== External links ==\n{{Medical resources\n| DiseasesDB      = 34928\n| ICD10           = \n| ICD9            = \n| ICDO            = \n| OMIM            = 231095\n| MedlinePlus     = \n| eMedicineSubj   = \n| eMedicineTopic  = \n| MeshID          = \n| Orphanet        = 1802\n}}\n{{Eicosanoid metabolism disorders}}\n\n[[Category:Eicosanoid metabolism disorders]]\n\n\n{{endocrine-disease-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox medical condition (new)\n| name            = Ghosal hematodiaphyseal dysplasia\n| synonyms        = GHDD<ref>{{cite web |title=OMIM Entry - # 231095 - GHOSAL HEMATODIAPHYSEAL DYSPLASIA; GHDD |url=https://omim.org/entry/231095 |website=omim.org |accessdate=14 April 2019}}</ref>\n| image           = Thromboxane A2 acsv.svg\n| alt             = \n| caption         = [[Thromboxane A2]]\n| pronounce       = \n| field           = \n| symptoms        = \n| complications   = \n| onset           = \n| duration        = \n| types           = \n| causes          = \n| risks           = \n| diagnosis       = \n| differential    = \n| prevention      = \n| treatment       = \n| medication      = \n| prognosis       = \n| frequency       = \n| deaths          = \n}}\n'''Ghosal hematodiaphyseal dysplasia,''' is a rare, [[Autosome|autosomal]] recessive disease, characterized by diaphyseal dysplasia and metaphyseal dysplasia of the long bones and refractory [[anemia]].<ref name=\"pmid17203301\">{{cite journal |last1=Isidor |first1=B. |last2=Dagoneau |first2=N. |last3=Huber |first3=C. |last4=Genevieve |first4=D. |last5=Bader-Meunier |first5=B. |last6=Blanche |first6=S. |last7=Picard |first7=C. |last8=De Vernejoul |first8=M. C. |last9=Munnich |first9=A. |last10=Le Merrer |first10=M. |last11=Cormier-Daire |first11=V. |title=A gene responsible for Ghosal hemato-diaphyseal dysplasia maps to chromosome 7q33\u201334 |journal=Human Genetics |date=3 January 2007 |volume=121 |issue=2 |pages=269\u2013273 |doi=10.1007/s00439-006-0311-1 |pmid=17203301 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Alebouyeh |first1=Mardawig |last2=Vossough |first2=Parvanch |last3=Tabarrok |first3=Firouz |title=Early Manifestation of Ghosal-Type Hemato-Diaphyseal Dysplasia |journal=Pediatric Hematology and Oncology |date=9 July 2009 |volume=20 |issue=5 |pages=409\u2013415 |doi=10.1080/08880010390203945 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://omim.org/clinicalSynopsis/231095|title=OMIM Clinical Synopsis - #231095 - GHOSAL HEMATODIAPHYSEAL DYSPLASIA; GHDD|website=omim.org|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\nIt is associated with a deficiency of [[Thromboxane-A synthase]],<ref name=\"pmid18264100\">{{cite journal |last1=Genevi\u00e8ve |first1=David |last2=Proulle |first2=Val\u00e9rie |last3=Isidor |first3=Bertrand |last4=Bellais |first4=Samuel |last5=Serre |first5=Val\u00e9rie |last6=Djouadi |first6=Fatima |last7=Picard |first7=Capucine |last8=Vignon-Savoye |first8=Capucine |last9=Bader-Meunier |first9=Brigitte |last10=Blanche |first10=St\u00e9phane |last11=de Vernejoul |first11=Marie-Christine |last12=Legeai-Mallet |first12=Laurence |last13=Fischer |first13=Anne-Marie |last14=Le Merrer |first14=Martine |last15=Dreyfus |first15=Marie |last16=Gaussem |first16=Pascale |last17=Munnich |first17=Arnold |last18=Cormier-Daire |first18=Val\u00e9rie |title=Thromboxane synthase mutations in an increased bone density disorder (Ghosal syndrome) |journal=Nature Genetics |date=10 February 2008 |volume=40 |issue=3 |pages=284\u2013286 |doi=10.1038/ng.2007.66 |pmid=18264100 }}</ref> which produces [[Thromboxane A2]].\n\nAlthough this disease is like [[Camurati\u2013Engelmann disease|Camurati-Engelman disease]] where there is also diaphyseal dysplasia, there are, however, reasons to differentiate between the two diseases. As mentioned earlier, both diseases affect diaphysis, but Ghosal hematodiaphyseal dysplasia, affects both the diaphysis, and metaphyses are affected.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://omim.org/entry/231095|title=OMIM Entry - # 231095 - GHOSAL HEMATODIAPHYSEAL DYSPLASIA; GHDD|website=omim.org|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> Also, [[Camurati\u2013Engelmann disease|Camurati-Engelman disease]] has no sign of defective [[Haematopoiesis|hematopoiesis]], but Ghosal hematodiaphyseal dysplasia is associated with a [[Hematologic disease|hematological abnormality]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Datta |first1=Kalpana |last2=Karmakar |first2=Madan |last3=Hira |first3=Michael |last4=Halder |first4=Sanjay |last5=Pramanik |first5=Koushik |last6=Banerjee |first6=Goutam |title=Ghosal Hematodiaphyseal Dysplasia with Myelofibrosis |journal=The Indian Journal of Pediatrics |date=15 September 2012 |volume=80 |issue=12 |pages=1050\u20131052 |doi=10.1007/s12098-012-0872-z |pmid=22983925 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Arora |first1=Richa |last2=Aggarwal |first2=Shagun |last3=Deme |first3=Swaroopa |title=Ghosal hematodiaphyseal dysplasia\u2014a concise review including an illustrative patient |journal=Skeletal Radiology |date=30 August 2014 |volume=44 |issue=3 |pages=447\u2013450 |doi=10.1007/s00256-014-1989-0 |pmid=25172219 }}</ref>\n\nThis is a rare disease and was characterized in 1988, with not many cases reported.<ref name=\"pmid3385529\">{{cite journal |last1=Ghosal |first1=S.P. |last2=Mukherjee |first2=A.K. |last3=Mukherjee |first3=D. |last4=Ghosh |first4=A.K. |title=Diaphyseal dysplasia associated with anemia |journal=The Journal of Pediatrics |date=July 1988 |volume=113 |issue=1 |pages=49\u201357 |doi=10.1016/s0022-3476(88)80527-4 |pmid=3385529 }}</ref> Most cases are found in India and the Middle East area, likely meaning a shared gene pool.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Jeevan |first1=Amrit |last2=Doyard |first2=Mathilde |last3=Kabra |first3=Madhulika |last4=Daire |first4=Valerie Cormier |last5=Gupta |first5=Neerja |title=Ghosal type hematodiaphyseal dysplasia |journal=Indian Pediatrics |date=16 April 2016 |volume=53 |issue=4 |pages=347\u2013348 |doi=10.1007/s13312-016-0851-y |pmid=27156553 }}</ref>\n\n== Symptoms ==\n\n== Causes ==\nGhosal hematodiaphyseal dysplasia is an inherited [[Autosome|autosomal]] recessive disorder due to a [[mutation]] in both copies of the TBXAS1 gene on [[chromosome]] 7q34. The TBXAS1 gene codes for the enzyme [[Thromboxane-A synthase]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://omim.org/entry/274180|title=OMIM Entry - * 274180 - THROMBOXANE A SYNTHASE 1; TBXAS1|website=omim.org|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\nThis enzyme has a couple of essential functions in the body that, if removed, could lead to the symptoms observed with the disease. [[Thromboxane-A synthase]] is responsible for platelet aggregation and the regulation of bone mineral density. [[Thromboxane-A synthase]] regulates bone mineral density by influencing the two [[Gene|genes]] TNFSF\u2081\u2081 and TNFSF\u2081\u2081B, which encode for RANKL and osteoclastogenesis inhibitory factor in osteoblasts which, consequently, leads to [[Sclerosis (medicine)|sclerosis]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Ciftciler |first1=Rafiye |last2=Buyukas\u0131k |first2=Yahya |last3=Saglam |first3=Emine Arzu |last4=Haznedaroglu |first4=Ibrahim Celalettin |title=Ghosal hematodiaphyseal dysplasia with autoimmune anemia in two adult siblings |journal=Transfusion and Apheresis Science |date=1 August 2019 |volume=58 |issue=4 |pages=449\u2013452 |doi=10.1016/j.transci.2019.04.027 |pmid=31395426 }}</ref>\n\nThe refractory [[anemia]], also called [[corticosteroid]] sensitive [[anemia]], is likely due to fibrotic scarring or [[Sclerosis (medicine)|sclerosis]], which is the stiffening of the [[Tissue (biology)|tissue]] when organ-specific [[Tissue (biology)|tissue]] is replaced with [[connective tissue]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Arora |first1=Richa |last2=Aggarwal |first2=Shagun |last3=Deme |first3=Swaroopa |title=Ghosal hematodiaphyseal dysplasia\u2014a concise review including an illustrative patient |journal=Skeletal Radiology |date=30 August 2014 |volume=44 |issue=3 |pages=447\u2013450 |doi=10.1007/s00256-014-1989-0 |pmid=25172219 }}</ref>\n\n== Treatment ==\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n== External links ==\n{{Medical resources\n| DiseasesDB      = 34928\n| ICD10           = \n| ICD9            = \n| ICDO            = \n| OMIM            = 231095\n| MedlinePlus     = \n| eMedicineSubj   = \n| eMedicineTopic  = \n| MeshID          = \n| Orphanet        = 1802\n}}\n{{Eicosanoid metabolism disorders}}\n\n[[Category:Eicosanoid metabolism disorders]]\n\n\n{{endocrine-disease-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Cricastaneda", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixed grammar mistakes", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ghosal_hematodiaphyseal_dysplasia"}
